### Version
2.5.11

### Reproduction link
[https://codepen.io/zollero/pen/opbxXX](https://codepen.io/zollero/pen/opbxXX)

### Steps to reproduce
Prop validate in v2.5.11, does not allow the key of prop to be one out of `['type', 'default', 'required', 'validator']`, and throw a warning error. 

This happens  when the `prop` is an array of object. And I must validate the key of the element object.

For example:

```
export default {
  props: {
    forms: {
      type: Array,
      required: true,
      prop: {
        type: String,
        required: true
      },
      label: String,
      editable: {
        type: Boolean,
        default: false
      }
    }
  }
}
```
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8801894/34087867-c8a8ae3c-e3e0-11e7-8820-bfe5ef989bbf.png)

### What is expected?
Expect the key out of ['type', 'default', 'required', 'validator'] can be valid.


### What is actually happening?
The key out of ['type', 'default', 'required', 'validator'] is invalid.

